Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, which deals with the development and application of AI models. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of domain knowledge, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
